# TypeScript Backend Conventions

- Use Node.js + TypeScript strict style with `import`/`export` ESM syntax.
- Use `.js` extensions in local imports (NodeNext compatibility).
- ESM has no `__dirname`; use `path.dirname(fileURLToPath(import.meta.url))` for view/file paths.
- Keep one concern per file and follow the project layout:
  - `src/routes/*` for Express routes
  - `src/services/*` for integrations/business logic
  - `src/utils/*` for utilities
  - `src/types/*` for shared types
  - `src/views/*` for HTML templates
- Prefer `const`; avoid `var`; use `let` only when reassignment is required.
- Use `async/await` over `.then()` chains for async flow.
- Use `try/catch` with meaningful error messages; never swallow errors silently.
- Add explicit return types on exported functions.
- Reuse shared types from `src/types` instead of inline duplicated types.
- Log with pino (`logger` from `src/utils/logger.ts`); use `info` in production, `debug` for local dev.
- Add short comments only when logic is non-obvious.
